026#39;s a reason Samsung is launching this phone later than the rest of its family, and that\u0026#39;s because it\u0026#39;s going to appeal to early adopters and not much else.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eFor its part, Samsung is referring to this launch as \u0026#34;more than a slim smartphone,\u0026#34; promoting the device as \u0026#34;setting a new standard for what you can achieve with your smartphone\u0026#34; while also bringing about a \u0026#34;new era of growth for the mobile industry.\u0026#34; So, you know, maybe you should forget what I said above and buy into the hype. Either way, we\u0026#39;ll find out together on May 12th.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eNot that you have to wait until next Monday if you\u0026#39;re exciting for the Edge. Right now, you can head over to Samsung\u0026#39;s website to reserve your own phone. Handing over your email address nets you a $50 credit for your eventual preorder. These bonuses usually only stick around up through the actual airing of Unpacked, so if you\u0026#39;re remotely interested in picking up the Galaxy S25 Edge at launch, make sure you click the link below to get your coupon.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                                \n        \n                            \n                                                            \n            \n            \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"7a61-40e5-bc093c164da0\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                            \n                        \t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/samsung-logo.png\" data-img-desc=\"\u0026#34;Source: Samsung\u0026#34;\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003c